This paper deals with neural models for Knowledge Base completion, which involves natural language processing and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories. The paper also proposes a new model that involves optimization and learning, which falls under cs.LG (Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with Knowledge Base data, which is related to databases, making cs.DB (Databases) a possible category as well.
